column260: It was a little difficult to determine how long ago some of the experiences were, since some of them were recurring experiences or experiences that occurred over a long period of time. I tried to base my timing for those off of what exactly I thought of while I was in the scanner.
column261: I totally could've taken more time to tell my life story in the scanner. Five minutes kind of didn't feel like enough. Also, I found myself narrating my experiences in my head when I was imagining them...that felt necessary to recalling/imagining them, which I think is kind of interesting. This is such a cool study!!! Oh, also the buttons on the button box were a little confusing...I think it would've made more sense if the thumb was 1 and the pinky was 5. And I think I could've used some more time to think about how I felt about the experiences after I imagined them.
